🎯 Why Random is Used in Java
The Random class is used when you want to:

Generate random numbers (integers, doubles, booleans, etc.)

Simulate randomness in games, testing, simulations, etc.

Add unpredictability to decisions (like shuffling cards or selecting a random item)

Create mock data for testing applications

🔧 Where It’s Commonly Used
Use Case	Example
🎮 Games	Dice rolls, card shuffling, enemy movements
🧪 Testing	Generate random test data (e.g., names, numbers)
🎲 Simulations	Weather, traffic, stock prediction
🧠 AI/ML	Random sampling, stochastic processes
📱 Apps	OTP generation, random question selection



package randomclass;
import java.util.Random;


public class random {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Random random = new Random();
		int number;
		double number1;
		boolean isHeads;
		number = random.nextInt(1,100);//integer values
		number1 = random.nextDouble(1,500);//double values
		isHeads = random.nextBoolean();//boolean values
		
		System.out.println(isHeads);
		System.out.println(number1);
		System.out.println(number);

	}

}

OUTPUT:
true
424.4275052799784
73
